This computation is only possible if the above polynomials were evenly divisible, because in that case the quotient formula_25 is a polynomial, not a rational function. Due to the construction of the trapdoor, it is not possible to evaluate a rational function at the trapdoor value, only to evaluate a polynomial using linear combinations of the precomputed known constants of formula_103. This is why it is impossible to create a proof for an incorrect value of formula_64.

